---
import Cta from '../../components/home/Cta-ContactShort.astro';
import SlotBlog from '../../components/home/Slot-Blog.astro';
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  description="Local SEO strategies that actually work for Gold Coast businesses in 2025. Real data and results from our client campaigns."
  title="Everything We Know About Ranking Locally on the Gold Coast · Blog · Aidxn Design"
>

    <SlotBlog>
      <Fragment slot="category">
        SEO and Digital Marketing
      </Fragment>
      <Fragment slot="title">
        Everything We Know About Ranking Locally on the Gold Coast
      </Fragment>

      <Fragment slot="cover">
        <div class="w-full h-48 rounded bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-600/20 to-cyan-500/20 flex items-center justify-center">
          <span class="text-4xl">&#128205;</span>
        </div>
      </Fragment>

      <Fragment slot="smlTitle">
        We Analysed Our Client Data — Here Is What Moves the Needle
      </Fragment>
      <Fragment slot="content">
        Local SEO advice on the internet is 90% recycled nonsense from 2019. "Claim your Google Business Profile" — yes, obviously. "Get more reviews" — groundbreaking insight. We wanted to share what actually moves rankings for Gold Coast businesses in 2025, based on real data from our client campaigns.

        Google Business Profile Is Still King
        Let us get the obvious one out of the way. Your Google Business Profile is still the single most important factor for local search visibility. But here is what most guides miss: it is not just about claiming it — it is about treating it like a living, breathing marketing channel. We post weekly updates for our clients. We upload fresh photos monthly. We respond to every single review within 24 hours. We use the Q&A section proactively, posting and answering common questions before customers ask them. The businesses that treat their GBP as actively as their Instagram consistently outrank those that set it and forget it.

        Page Speed Is a Local Ranking Factor
        This is the one most local SEO agencies completely ignore because they cannot fix it. If your website loads slowly, you rank lower. Full stop. We rebuilt a Gold Coast tradie's site from WordPress to Astro and watched their local pack ranking go from position seven to position three within six weeks. The only change was page speed. Same content, same backlinks, same reviews. Google's algorithm favours fast sites, and most local business websites are embarrassingly slow.

        Reviews Matter — But Recency Matters More
        Having 200 reviews from 2022 is worth less than having 40 reviews from the last three months. Google weights review recency heavily in local rankings. We help our clients set up automated review request flows — a simple SMS or email sent 24 hours after a job is completed. The businesses that consistently generate two to three reviews per week outperform competitors with higher overall review counts but stale profiles.

        Location Pages Are Not Dead
        If you serve multiple suburbs on the Gold Coast, you should have dedicated pages for each service area. Not thin doorway pages stuffed with keywords — genuine, useful pages with specific information about serving that area. A plumber in Burleigh Heads should have a page that mentions Burleigh-specific details, not just a template with the suburb name swapped in. We create location pages that include local landmarks, common issues specific to that area, and genuine service details. Google can tell the difference between a lazy template and a real page.

        Backlinks Still Matter Locally
        Everyone wants to ignore backlinks because building them is tedious. But local backlinks from Gold Coast directories, local news sites, community organisations, and industry associations still move the needle significantly. We have found that five quality local backlinks are worth more than fifty random directory submissions. Get listed with your local chamber of commerce, sponsor a community event, write a guest post for a local blog. These are not scalable tactics, but they work.

        Schema Markup Is Free Money
        LocalBusiness schema markup takes about fifteen minutes to implement and gives Google explicit structured data about your business — name, address, phone number, operating hours, service areas, reviews. Most local businesses do not have it. Every single one of our client sites does, and it consistently correlates with improved search visibility. It is genuinely the highest-ROI SEO task you can do.

        What Does Not Work Anymore
        Keyword stuffing your page titles. Buying links from overseas directories. Creating dozens of thin location pages. Fake reviews. Google's spam detection has improved dramatically in 2025, and we have seen competitors penalised for tactics that used to work fine. Play the long game. Build a fast website, earn real reviews, create genuine content, and show up consistently. It is not exciting advice, but it is what the data shows.

      </Fragment>
    </SlotBlog>

  <Cta />

</Layout>
